NEWS - list of user-visible changes between releases of apt-rdepends

New in 1.3.0:
* By default, dependencies will catch Depends and Pre-Depends, because
  that's the expected semantic.
* Now supports VCG output, with the --vcg option.

New in 1.2.0:
* Non-English locales work now!
* You can now search for recursive build dependencies.

New in 1.1.0:
* You can now choose to see a dependency tree for only the packages
  installed on your system.  Use the --state-show and --state-follow
  options.
* You can now see the current state of packages.  Use the --print-state
  options.
